### ==============================================
### Error Scenarios
### ==============================================

### Unauthorized Create (Non-Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reference-data/focus-areas
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Unauthorized Focus Area"
}

# Expected Response (401):
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "error": {
#     "code": "UNAUTHORIZED",
#     "message": "Admin access required"
#   }
# }

### Duplicate Entry
POST {{baseUrl}}/reference-data/amenities
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "WiFi"
}

# Expected Response (400):
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "error": {
#     "code": "DUPLICATE_ENTRY",
#     "message": "Amenity with this name already exists"
#   }
# }

### Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/reference-data/skills/non-existent-id

# Expected Response (404):
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "error": {
#     "code": "NOT_FOUND",
#     "message": "Skill not found"
#   }
# }

### ==============================================
### Testing Notes
### ==============================================

# Authentication:
# - GET operations are public (no auth required)
# - POST, PATCH, DELETE require admin authentication

# Seeding:
# Use: npm run db:seed to populate reference data

# Categories:
# - Amenities: connectivity, convenience, safety, recreation
# - Facilities: workspace, equipment, event, wellness
# - Skills: programming, design, business, marketing
# - Job Preferences: employment_type, work_mode, industry
